    <id>http://forestrick.github.io/blog/2015/02/07/github-page-with-octopress</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2>Github Setup</h2>

<p>Go to your github page and create a repository
naming it to <strong>{username.github.io}</strong></p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ git clone https://github.com/{username}/{username}.github.io</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Test it</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ echo "Hello World" &gt; index.html
</span><span class='line'>$ git add â€”all
</span><span class='line'>$ git commit -m "Initial commit"
</span><span class='line'>$ git push</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<hr />

<h2>Installation</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle install 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake install 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake preview </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<!--more-->


<h2>Setting up for github pages</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake setup_github_pages
</span><span class='line'>$ rake deploy</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Make a new post</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake new_post[title]</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Translate markdown to html file</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake generate</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Remove page</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rm -rf [pages] 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake generate 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake deploy</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Read on Buttons in Index Page</h2>

<p>Check your _config.yml and find <strong>excerpt_separator</strong>
default value is: <strong>&lt;!&ndash;more&ndash;></strong>
add <strong>&lt;!&ndash;more&ndash;></strong> to the paragraph that your want show in index page</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>excerpt_separator: "&lt;!--more--&gt;"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>e.g.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>## Installation
</span><span class='line'>$ git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle install 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake install 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake preview 
</span><span class='line'>&lt;!--more--&gt;</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<hr />

<h2>Install lucaslew/whitespace theme</h2>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ cd octopress
</span><span class='line'>$ git clone git://github.com/lucaslew/whitespace.git .themes/whitespace
</span><span class='line'># for zsh, use: rake install\['whitespace'\]
</span><span class='line'>$ rake install['whitespace'] 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake generate</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<hr />

<p>References:
<a href="https://pages.github.com/">Github Page</a>
<a href="http://octopress.org/docs/setup/">Octopress Setup</a>
<a href="https://github.com/lucaslew/whitespace">lucaslew/whitespace github page</a></p>
]]></content>
